<ul>
<li><ins><b>What does the Time Sheet feature help me do?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">People work on projects and need a place to log how much time a particular task, issue or an action has taken. 
Sometime these need to be invoiced to clients as billable or non-billable. 
The Time Sheet feature helps you log all time associated within a project by different team members in one central location.</font>  
</ul>

<ul>
<li><ins><b>Why is it required to enter timesheet regularly?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">You will have a systematic track on your timesheet and also you will spend less time in disputes and
 less time trying to remember what actually you had worked on.</font>  
</ul>

<ul>
<li><ins><b>How do I record time in a project?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">You can select relevant category from drop down list and enter your actual hours spent. Enter the work done in detail in the description area.
 This will help you and your leads to keep track on your project related work. Your timesheet dashboard can be exported to excel file. </font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>Why is it required to log acutal hours?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">To recognize the effort spent by you.</font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>How to take comp offs?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">Select comp off from the list and add your onsite/lead approval status in description field.</font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>In what format can I log time?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">You can either enter a number of a number and a decimal.
 To enter 2 hours and 30 minutes you would enter 2.30. To enter 1 hour 15 minutes you would enter 1.15 mins.</font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>If I delete a task or issue, does the time associated with it also get deleted from the time sheet page?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">Yes, the time will be removed from the time sheet page. </font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>If we do not have backlog and task ID?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">Enter the field as NA or TBD [If the ids will be created in future].</font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>Do I need to enter additional hours spent in a day?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">Yes.</font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>Do I need to enter the time I spend during weekends?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">Yes, with the actual hours spent for the day.</font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>On public holidays, do we have to mark working hours?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">Select public holiday from category list and save the auto filled entries.
 If you have worked for the day select relevant category from list and make appropriate entry.</font>  
</ul>
<ul>
<li><ins><b>Do I have to enter leaves in timesheet?</b></ins></li>
<font color="#585858">Yes. Select leave from the category list and enter 0.0 hours.</font>  
</ul>

